        <div class="block">
            <h2>What is the One World Marathon?</h2>
            <p>One World Strong Foundation embodies the core principles of connection and co-operation, supporting the belief that people around the world should work together toward common goals.</p>
            <p>To reinforce that message, we’ve proposed a marathon, where teams of participants from around the world will combine their efforts to achieve a total of 26.2 miles (or 42.195km) over a four-day event. Participants apply and sign-up for a distance they will contribute on the event dates.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="block">
            <h2>Who can participate?</h2>
            <p>All are welcome, but we especially encourage young people to participate through their schools, colleges and universities, to reinforce the value of making connections, showing curiosity toward other cultures and collaborating toward common goals.</p>
            <p>The event is open to all abilities, assisted or unassisted, mobility impaired, teams or individual participants. We aim to have someone from every country in the world participate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="block">
            <h2>What’s your ultimate aim from the event?</h2>
            <p>One World Marathon's main objective is to connect people across borders and diverse backgrounds.&nbsp; We encourage teams that represent multiple continents, countries, and cultures. We hope to&nbsp;inspire people to see the benefits of working together as a global community and encourage others to develop similar&nbsp;projects.</p>
            <p>In the long term, we aim to implement a strong, unified, virtual platform, whose message of connectivity and openness contradicts the basic premises of racism, bigotry, violent extremist and terrorist rhetoric.&nbsp;Furthermore, we endeavor to promote a healthy and active lifestyle, global interconnectivity and resiliency for individuals and communities impacted by trauma.</p>
            <p>The implementation of a strong, unified virtual platform, whose message of connectivity and openness contradicts the basic premises of violent extremist and terrorist rhetoric. The promotion of a healthy and active lifestyle, global interconnectivity and resiliency for individuals and communities impacted by trauma.</p>
            <p>One World Marathon’s aim is to inspire people to see the benefits of working together as a global community, and encourage others to develop similar projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="block">
            <h2>When is it happening?</h2>
            <p>Between April 12th - April 15th</p>
            <p>The One World Marathon will start on April 12th with the RunJordan Dead Sea Ultra Marathon at 6am and it will end when the Boston Marathon’s final participant, and our Global Race Director Dave McGillivray crosses the finish line – approximately midnight EST on April 15th.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
